This skill teaches AI agents the user's conventions for installing,
updating, and editing other agent skills. It does not itself execute
any installs or edits — it provides guidance to the agent invoking
it. The agent is responsible for executing the documented commands
on the user's machine.

By installing or using this skill, you acknowledge that:

1. The conventions encoded here (canonical -a flags, no tool-bundled
   installers, edit-via-source) are opinionated and reflect one
   user's setup. They may not match your own workflow.
2. Following the documented end-to-end flows will create or modify
   files under ~/.agents/skills/, ~/.claude/skills/, and
   ~/.agents/.skill-lock.json. Review the commands before running
   them if you are not certain of their effect.
3. The "create a new skill" flow creates a public GitHub repository
   by default, which is irreversible (deleting the repo afterward
   does not remove copies that may have been cloned or indexed).
